&lt;p&gt;University Hospitals of Morecambe Bay Foundation Trust provides acute hospital care to the local population. We are located on the edge of the beautiful Lake District.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a registered nurse with previous experience seeking a new challenge?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a change?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you soon to be a newly qualified nurse looking for a great preceptorship to support the start of your nursing career?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you like the thought of a fast paced, challenging job, then we would like to hear from you. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Come on join our ever developing strong team of diverse nurses serving a wide range of medical conditions from acute care to quality end of life care. Full support will be given for you to achieve your developmental potential.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Newly qualified Band 5 nurses are welcomed to apply;where you can work towards Band 5 competencies &amp; develop extended roles. Full support for Preceptorship given.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Anyone newly appointed to the trust will be subject to the completion of a satisfactory 6 month probationary period (this includes bank staff). This will give the new staff member an opportunity to become familiar with the role and working environment.&lt;/p&gt;
